ent, walking the precarious bridge between allegiance to Israel and the Jewish people and the universal rights of all people. This collection of old and new essays combines theory, sociology, film studies, literary criticism, post-modern thought, and politics to understand our present situation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aJewish radicals. 0aZionism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Human Rights.2bisacsh  a1960s.  aHolocaust.  aIsrael.  aJewish radical.  aNew Left.  aYiddish culture.  aZionism.  aactivism.  aantisemitism.  afascism.  agenocide.  ahippies.  aliberation.  aneo-Nazism.  apolitics.  aprogressivism.  aracism.  areform.  asocial change.  asocialism.  asociology.1 aMagid, Shaul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068820708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644694657zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644694657423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781644694657.jpg  a978-3-11-068820-7  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP 